# Executive Summary  
Merging the landing (index.html) and buyer portal (buyer.html) pages requires resolving overlapping storage keys and unifying the UI flows. Key risks include **data conflicts** (both use `mei_properties_v1` and `mei_leads_v1`), **UX complexity** (multiple filters, lead forms, and modals on one page), **accessibility** (ensuring focus outlines, skip links, and contrast meet WCAG AA), and **privacy** (storing buyer info in localStorage requires DPDP compliance). High-impact fixes (P0) include adding a “Skip to content” link【12†L19-L27】, ensuring all controls meet target size (≥24×24 px)【17†L140-L149】 and contrast (≥4.5:1)【19†L41-L44】, and providing visible focus indicators【15†L33-L36】. Secondary fixes (P1/P2) cover adding ARIA roles (e.g. `role="status"` for toasts), OTP/email field attributes, and confirming data handling aligns with privacy guidelines.  

## Prioritized Changes (P0/P1/P2)

| Priority | Change & Rationale                                           | Effort |
|:--------:|:-------------------------------------------------------------|:------:|
| **P0**   | **Skip link to main** – Add a “Skip to main content” link at top【12†L19-L27】 for keyboard users (WCAG 2.4.1). | Medium |
| **P0**   | **Focus visible** – Ensure keyboard focus outlines are clearly visible (WCAG 2.4.7)【15†L33-L36】.  | Medium |
| **P0**   | **Contrast ≥4.5:1** – Text/buttons meet 4.5:1 contrast ratio【19†L41-L44】.  | Low   |
| **P0**   | **Target size ≥24px** – All interactive targets at least 24×24 CSS px【17†L140-L149】 (AA SC 2.5.8). | Low   |
| **P1**   | **ARIA/live roles** – Mark status messages with `role="status"` so screen readers announce them.       | Low   |
| **P1**   | **Secure links** – Use `rel="noopener noreferrer"` on outbound links and avoid `target=_blank` without it. | Low  |
| **P1**   | **Form attributes** – Use `type="tel"`, `inputmode`, `autocomplete=one-time-code` for phone/OTP (NIST SP 800-63B recommends auto-fill)【turn3search8†L0-L5】. | Low |
