| **P2**   | **Privacy note** – Acknowledge DPDP (Indian data protection) by avoiding storage of more PII than needed; use secure cookies server-side (unspecified). | Low   |

*Thresholds:* Apply WCAG 2.1 AA: contrast ≥4.5:1【19†L41-L44】, focus visible【15†L33-L36】, target size ≥24px【17†L140-L149】. For OTP/login (future enhancements), follow NIST SP800-63B (TTL 300s, resend ≥30s, max 5 attempts, 2m lockout) and set file upload limits (≤5 MB, max 3 MB per file) per OWASP guidance. Cite WCAG and OWASP for practices【12†L19-L27】【15†L33-L36】.

## Merge Plan

- **Storage Keys:** `mei_properties_v1` (approved listings), `mei_leads_v1` (all leads), plus demo keys `mei_brokers_v1` and `mei_whatsapp_template_v1` from admin UI. The buyer portal originally used `mei_properties_v1` for listing data and `mei_leads_v1` for new leads. The index (landing) page did _not_ use localStorage; it posted leads via API. For the merge, we will store new leads in `mei_leads_v1` if offline. Admin actions (add-property) already populate `mei_properties_v1`. No key conflicts beyond these.
- **UI Unification:** The merged page’s header/nav has sections for **Home**, **Listings**, **Post Lead**, and **Join as Broker**. The main section will combine:
  - **Hero (Landing):** Hero text, KPI chips.
  - **Lead Form:** “Post a Lead” form with name, phone, type, locality, budget, notes.
  - **Broker Form:** “Join as Broker” KYC form with name, phone, area, experience, etc.
  - **Buyer Portal:** Search/filter grid of approved listings and an “Interested” modal (lead modal).
- Use a section or article for each part and anchor links in nav (`href="#listings"` etc).
- **Conflicts:** Resolve by single localStorage sync routine. For example, `refreshListings()` pulls `mei_properties_v1` for approved listings (landing was static demo listings), and `refreshLeads()` manages `mei_leads_v1`. Ensure one master list of leads (merge index’s API path and buyer’s localStorage path).
- **API-mode toggle:** Add an “API mode” button that would flip between offline demo (localStorage) and (unimplemented) API calls. For offline, fill `mei_properties_v1` and `mei_leads_v1` as needed. Mark in code where actual `fetch()` calls should go (unspecified endpoints).
- **Offline queue:** If offline (e.g. via `navigator.onLine` false), queue lead/broker submissions in `localStorage` (e.g. a `mei_offline_queue` key). Show user a “You are offline” message. Once online, attempt retries (pseudocode comment).
- **Data flow:** Index’s lead/broker forms on submit will either `POST /leads` and `POST /brokers/onboard` via `fetch`, or if offline, save to queue. Buyer “Request” button (lead modal) creates a lead in `mei_leads_v1` immediately (mimics “POST /leads”). Approved listings on buyer portal come from `mei_properties_v1` (only “approved” items). Unspecified: Storage backend for listings (we assume localStorage suffices for demo).
- **Unknowns:** Actual API endpoints, server implementation for DPDP compliance, and real authentication flows (index’s OTP hint) are marked as TODO. All code will comment "// TODO: connect to backend API".

